ages of Taiwan]]\n", "name_user": "Popcornfud", "label": "safe", "comment": "ce", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_language"}
{"title_page": "Morano Calabro", "text_new": "{{Infobox Italian comune\n| name                = Morano Calabro\n| official_name       = Comune di Morano Calabro\n| native_name         = \n| image_skyline       = Morano Calabro.jpg\n| imagesize           = \n| image_alt           = \n| image_caption       = \n| image_shield        = Morano Calabro-Stemma.png\n| shield_alt          = \n| image_map           = \n| map_alt             = \n| map_caption         = \n| pushpin_label_position = \n| pushpin_map_alt     = \n| coordinates         = {{coord|39|51|N|16|8|E|region:IT|display=inline}}\n| coordinates_footnotes = \n| region              = [[Calabria]]\n| province            = [[province of Cosenza|Cosenza]] (CS)\n| frazioni            = [[Campotenese]]\n| mayor_party         = \n| mayor               = Nicol\u00f2 De Bartolo\n| area_footnotes      = \n| area_total_km2      = 112.34\n| population_footnotes = <ref name=\"istat\">All demographics and other statistics from the Italian statistical institute ([[National Institute of Statistics (Italy)|Istat]])</ref>\n| population_total    = 4608\n| population_as_of    = 30 August 2012\n| pop_density_footnotes = \n| population_demonym  = Moranesi\n| elevation_footnotes = \n| elevation_min_m     =\n| elevation_max_m     =\n| elevation_m         = 694\n| twin1               = \n| twin1_country       = \n| saint               = Saint [[Bernardino of Siena]]\n| day                 = 20 May \n| postal_code         = 87016\n| area_code           = 0981\n| website             = {{official website|http://www.comunemoranocalabro.it/}}\n| footnotes           =\n}}\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=Malik Mudasir Arian|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>'''Malik Mudasir Arian Calabro''' ([[Northern Calabrian|Moranese]]: {{lang|nap|Murenu}} {{IPA-nap|mu\u02c8r\u025b\u02d0nu|}}) is a town and ''[[comune]]'' in the [[province of Cosenza]] in the [[Calabria]] region of southern [[Italy]]. It was  the birthplace of mathematician [[Gaetano Scorza]].\n[[File:Morano Calabro view.jpg|thumb|240px|View of Morano Calabro.]]\n[[File:NormanFort.jpg|thumb|240px|Norman fortress built on Roman ruins in Morano Calabro.]]\n\n==Geography==\nThe municipality borders with [[Castrovillari]] (the nearest town), [[Mormanno]], [[Rotonda, Basilicata|Rotonda]], [[San Basile]], [[Saracena]], [[Terranova di Pollino]] and [[Viggianello]].\n\n===Campotenese===\nIts ''[[frazione]]'' (civil parish), the village of [[Campotenese]], is located on a mountain pass at 1,015 [[Above mean sea level|amsl]]. A tourist site, the village is best known for the [[Battle of Campo Tenese]] (1806) between the [[First French Empire]] and the [[Kingdom of Naples]]. {{Citation needed|date=April 2012}}\n\n==Sister cities==\n* {{flagicon|Brazil}} [[Porto Alegre]], [[Brazil]]<ref>{{in lang|it}} [http://www.comuni-italiani.it/078/083/ Infos about the twinnage Morano-Porto Alegre (www.comuni-italiani.it)]</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Battle of Campo Tenese]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{commonscatinline}}\n*[http://www.comunemoranocalabro.it Official website {{in lang|it}}]\n<BR>\n{{Province of Cosenza}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Calabria]]\n\n\n{{Calabria-geo-stub}}\n.\nMalik Mudasir Arian\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Italian comune\n| name                = Morano Calabro\n| official_name       = Comune di Morano Calabro\n| native_name         = \n| image_skyline       = Morano Calabro.jpg\n| imagesize           = \n| image_alt           = \n| image_caption       = \n| image_shield        = Morano Calabro-Stemma.png\n| shield_alt          = \n| image_map           = \n| map_alt             = \n| map_caption         = \n| pushpin_label_position = \n| pushpin_map_alt     = \n| coordinates         = {{coord|39|51|N|16|8|E|region:IT|display=inline}}\n| coordinates_footnotes = \n| region              = [[Calabria]]\n| province            = [[province of Cosenza|Cosenza]] (CS)\n| frazioni            = [[Campotenese]]\n| mayor_party         = \n| mayor               = Nicol\u00f2 De Bartolo\n| area_footnotes      = \n| area_total_km2      = 112.34\n| population_footnotes = <ref name=\"istat\">All demographics and other statistics from the Italian statistical institute ([[National Institute of Statistics (Italy)|Istat]])</ref>\n| population_total    = 4608\n| population_as_of    = 30 August 2012\n| pop_density_footnotes = \n| population_demonym  = Moranesi\n| elevation_footnotes = \n| elevation_min_m     =\n| elevation_max_m     =\n| elevation_m         = 694\n| twin1               = \n| twin1_country       = \n| saint               = Saint [[Bernardino of Siena]]\n| day                 = 20 May \n| postal_code         = 87016\n| area_code           = 0981\n| website             = {{official website|http://www.comunemoranocalabro.it/}}\n| footnotes           =\n}}\n'''Morano Calabro''' ([[Northern Calabrian|Moranese]]: {{lang|nap|Murenu}} {{IPA-nap|mu\u02c8r\u025b\u02d0nu|}}) is a town and ''[[comune]]'' in the [[province of Cosenza]] in the [[Calabria]] region of southern [[Italy]]. It was  the birthplace of mathematician [[Gaetano Scorza]].\n[[File:Morano Calabro view.jpg|thumb|240px|View of Morano Calabro.]]\n[[File:NormanFort.jpg|thumb|240px|Norman fortress built on Roman ruins in Morano Calabro.]]\n\n==Geography==\nThe municipality borders with [[Castrovillari]] (the nearest town), [[Mormanno]], [[Rotonda, Basilicata|Rotonda]], [[San Basile]], [[Saracena]], [[Terranova di Pollino]] and [[Viggianello]].\n\n===Campotenese===\nIts ''[[frazione]]'' (civil parish), the village of [[Campotenese]], is located on a mountain pass at 1,015 [[Above mean sea level|amsl]]. A tourist site, the village is best known for the [[Battle of Campo Tenese]] (1806) between the [[First French Empire]] and the [[Kingdom of Naples]]. {{Citation needed|date=April 2012}}\n\n==Sister cities==\n* {{flagicon|Brazil}} [[Porto Alegre]], [[Brazil